                            <comment id="12558523" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 07:14:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Billy, wouldn&apos;t it be better making REST and thrift work the same as hbase master and regionserver taking the same &apos;start&apos; parameter rather than special-case thrift and REST in the start-daemon.sh script?  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-297&quot; title=&quot;hbase rest server should be started with hbase-daemon.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-297&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-2545&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a near-duplicate of this issue, asks that it be possible to specify alternate Configuration for REST (and thrift) servers (I&apos;ll have a go at a patch unless you beat me too it).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12558544" author="viper799" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 09:04:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no go ahead I will close this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would rather have a start/stop option on the rest server then make changes to the start script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Billy&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12558692" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 17:46:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to make rest and thrift do same as master and regionserver so both can be started/stopped via hbase-daemon.sh and logs go into files named for daemon in $HADOOP_LOG_DIR. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
